'''2020年韓國洪災'''是自2020年6月以来，由於[[朝鲜半岛|朝鲜半岛]]南部持續的[[梅雨|梅雨]]，[[朝鲜民主主义人民共和国|朝鲜民主主义人民共和国]]部分地區和[[大韩民国|大韩民国]]大部分地区發生嚴重洪災。而同時期受梅雨影響，[[2020年中国南方水灾|中国南方]]以及[[2020年7月日本水災|日本九州]]也出現洪災。 {{As of|2020|08|9}}，[[韓國|韓國]]已有38人因災死亡<ref name="Join0809">{{Cite web|title=9일째 이어진 폭우, 사상자 속출…30명 숨지고 12명 실종|url=https://news.joins.com/article/23844172|date=9 August 2020|publisher=JoongAng Ilbo|accessdate=2020-08-09|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106070616/https://news.joins.com/article/23844172|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="CNA-08-08">[https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/south-korea-floods-landslides-kill-26-as-heavy-rains-continue-13002910 "South Korea floods, landslides kill 26 as heavy rains continue."] {{Wayback|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/south-korea-floods-landslides-kill-26-as-heavy-rains-continue-13002910 |date=20210106070620 }} Channel News Asia. (Reuters) 8 August 2020. Retrieved 9 August 2020.</ref>。

2020年6月下旬，韩国進入雨季。<ref>Ko Jun-tae. [http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200623000830 "2020 monsoon season to start Wednesday."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200623000830 |date=20210106070632 }} ''The Korea Herald.'' 23 June 2020. Retrieved 5 August 2020.</ref>7月初，大雨过后，[[釜山廣域市|釜山]]被洪水淹没。<ref>[https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200710007700315 "Busan soaked by sixth-heaviest downpour in two decades."] {{Wayback|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200710007700315 |date=20210106070631 }} Yonhap News Agency. 10 July 2020. Retrieved 5 August 2020.</ref>7月下旬，韩国东南部地区出現狂風暴雨，導致數人死亡。<ref>[http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200724000271 "Heavy downpours pummel S. Korea, unleash flash floods, leave 4 dead or missing."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200724000271 |date=20210106070858 }} ''The Korea Herald.'' (Yonhap) 24 July 2020. Retrieved 5 August 2020.</ref>7月中旬，[[韓國氣象廳|韓國氣象廳]]一位官员表示，[[济州岛|济州岛]]早在6月10日就迎來雨季，而在6月24日，韓國南部和中部地区進入雨季。<ref>[https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200713005852315 "Southern South Korea hit by devastating downpours."] {{Wayback|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200713005852315 |date=20210106070633 }} Yonhap News Agency. 13 July 2020. Retrieved 5 August 2020.</ref>8月，持續的降雨給韓國南部地区帶來人員和財產損失。<ref name="CNA-08-08" /><ref>[https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/south-korea-flood-response-covid-19-12991436 "COVID-19 complicates South Korea flood response as hundreds gather in shelters."] {{Wayback|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/south-korea-flood-response-covid-19-12991436 |date=20210106070642 }} Channel News Asia. (Reuters) 5 August 2020. Retrieved 5 August 2020.</ref>

與此同時，[[朝鲜中央通讯社|朝鲜中央通讯社]]报道了[[朝鲜|朝鲜]]的災情，但没有提及人員遇難。<ref name="Star">[https://www.thestar.com.my/aseanplus/aseanplus-news/2020/08/08/food-supply-a-concern-amid-n-korea-floods "Food supply a concern amid N. Korea floods."] {{Wayback|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/aseanplus/aseanplus-news/2020/08/08/food-supply-a-concern-amid-n-korea-floods |date=20210106070658 }} ''The Star''. (Reuters) 8 August 2020. Retrieved 9 August 2020.</ref><ref name="CNA-08-08" />据报道，朝鮮最高领导人[[金正恩|金正恩]]在8月7日视察了与韩国相邻的[[黄海北道|黄海北道]]受灾地区。有人担心，此次洪災可能会影響朝鲜的粮食收成，并对該國的粮食安全构成威胁<ref name="CNA-08-08"/><ref name="Star"/>。

